{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775840769699,"sessionID":"ses_287a62ce1ffeBNBdkotu1qRClK","part":{"id":"prt_d785bb64a001fsMIN7HKL0BHwG","messageID":"msg_d785a5d5d001YvbqfpyLaKEN3m","sessionID":"ses_287a62ce1ffeBNBdkotu1qRClK","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-53502979858c4b7a9116ad513096a6a7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-003 — CRD 共享类型与常量\n\nModule: `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1`  \nLanguage: Go  \nSize: S\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nDefine shared types, constants, and CRD structures for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter custom resources in the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### REQ-001: Protocol Type Constants\n\n**GIVEN** the `shared_types.go` file defines protocol types for network ports  \n**WHEN** a developer needs to specify HTTP or HTTPS protocol  \n**THEN** the `ProtocolType` type and constants `ProtocolTypeHTTP` and `ProtocolTypeHTTPS` shall be available\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: HTTP protocol constant\nGIVEN the package v1alpha1 is imported\nWHEN ProtocolTypeHTTP is referenced\nTHEN it shall equal \"HTTP\"\n\n// Scenario 2: HTTPS protocol constant\nGIVEN the package v1alpha1 is imported\nWHEN ProtocolTypeHTTPS is referenced\nTHEN it shall equal \"HTTPS\"\n\n// Scenario 3: Protocol type can be used in struct fields\nGIVEN a TargetPort struct with Protocol field\nWHEN assigning ProtocolTypeHTTP to Protocol\nTHEN the value shall serialize to JSON as \"HTTP\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-002: Auth Mode Type Constants\n\n**GIVEN** the `shared_types.go` file defines authentication modes for CodeInterpreter  \n**WHEN** a developer needs to specify authentication mode  \n**THEN** the `AuthModeType` type and constants `AuthModePicoD` and `AuthModeNone` shall be available\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: PicoD auth mode constant\nGIVEN the package v1alpha1 is imported\nWHEN AuthModePicoD is referenced\nTHEN it shall equal \"picod\"\n\n// Scenario 2: None auth mode constant\nGIVEN the package v1alpha1 is imported\nWHEN AuthModeNone is referenced\nTHEN it shall equal \"none\"\n\n// Scenario 3: Auth mode validation via kubebuilder\nGIVEN a CodeInterpreterSpec with AuthMode field\nWHEN setting AuthMode to an invalid value\nTHEN kubebuilder validation Enum shall reject values other than \"picod\" or \"none\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-003: TargetPort Shared Struct\n\n**GIVEN** `TargetPort` defines network port configuration for exposing sandbox services  \n**WHEN** a CRD needs to specify exposed ports  \n**THEN** the struct shall contain PathPrefix, Name, Port, and Protocol fields with proper JSON tags and validation\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: TargetPort JSON serialization\nGIVEN a TargetPort with all fields populated\nWHEN marshaling to JSON\nTHEN the output shall contain \"pathPrefix\", \"name\", \"port\", \"protocol\" keys\n\n// Scenario 2: TargetPort Protocol default\nGIVEN a TargetPort with Protocol field\nWHEN kubebuilder processes the struct\nTHEN the default value shall be \"HTTP\"\n\n// Scenario 3: TargetPort Protocol enum validation\nGIVEN a TargetPort with Protocol field\nWHEN kubebuilder processes the struct\nTHEN only \"HTTP\" and \"HTTPS\" values shall be allowed\n\n// Scenario 4: TargetPort DeepCopy\nGIVEN a TargetPort instance with all fields set\nWHEN calling DeepCopy()\nTHEN a deep copy with identical values shall be returned\nAND modifying the copy shall not affect the original\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-004: GroupVersion and Scheme Registration\n\n**GIVEN** the API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`  \n**WHEN** types need to be registered with Kubernetes runtime scheme  \n**THEN** `GroupVersion`, `SchemeBuilder`, and `AddToScheme` shall be available\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: GroupVersion group\nGIVEN the v1alpha1 package\nWHEN accessing GroupVersion.Group\nTHEN it shall equal \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"\n\n// Scenario 2: GroupVersion version\nGIVEN the v1alpha1 package\nWHEN accessing GroupVersion.Version\nTHEN it shall equal \"v1alpha1\"\n\n// Scenario 3: AddToScheme function\nGIVEN the v1alpha1 package\nWHEN accessing AddToScheme\nTHEN it shall be a non-nil function of type func(*runtime.Scheme) error\n\n// Scenario 4: SchemeBuilder\nGIVEN the v1alpha1 package\nWHEN accessing SchemeBuilder\nTHEN it shall be a non-nil pointer to scheme.Builder\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-005: Kind Constants and GroupVersionKind Helpers\n\n**GIVEN** CRD types need Kind constants for type identification  \n**WHEN** a controller or client needs to reference CRD kinds  \n**THEN** Kind constants and GroupVersionKind helpers shall be available\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: AgentRuntime kind constant\nGIVEN the v1alpha1 package\nWHEN accessing AgentRuntimeKind\nTHEN it shall equal \"AgentRuntime\"\n\n// Scenario 2: AgentRuntimeList kind constant\nGIVEN the v1alpha1 package\nWHEN accessing AgentRuntimeListKind\nTHEN it shall equal \"AgentRuntimeList\"\n\n// Scenario 3: AgentRuntime GroupVersionKind\nGIVEN the v1alpha1 package\nWHEN accessing AgentRuntimeGroupVersionKind\nTHEN it shall have Group \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version \"v1alpha1\", Kind \"AgentRuntime\"\n\n// Scenario 4: CodeInterpreter kind constant\nGIVEN the v1alpha1 package\nWHEN accessing CodeInterpreterKind\nTHEN it shall equal \"CodeInterpreter\"\n\n// Scenario 5: CodeInterpreterList kind constant\nGIVEN the v1alpha1 package\nWHEN accessing CodeInterpreterListKind\nTHEN it shall equal \"CodeInterpreterList\"\n\n// Scenario 6: CodeInterpreter GroupVersionKind\nGIVEN the v1alpha1 package\nWHEN accessing CodeInterpreterGroupVersionKind\nTHEN it shall have Group \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version \"v1alpha1\", Kind \"CodeInterpreter\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-006: Resource Helper Function\n\n**GIVEN** controllers need GroupVersionResource for informers and listers  \n**WHEN** constructing a GroupVersionResource for a resource name  \n**THEN** the `Resource()` helper function shall return the correct GVR\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: AgentRuntime resource\nGIVEN the Resource function\nWHEN calling Resource(\"agentruntimes\")\nTHEN it shall return GroupVersionResource with Group \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\" and Resource \"agentruntimes\"\n\n// Scenario 2: CodeInterpreter resource\nGIVEN the Resource function\nWHEN calling Resource(\"codeinterpreters\")\nTHEN it shall return GroupVersionResource with Group \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\" and Resource \"codeinterpreters\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-007: AgentRuntime CRD Types\n\n**GIVEN** AgentRuntime represents a runtime configuration for an AI agent sandbox  \n**WHEN** defining the CRD structure  \n**THEN** `AgentRuntime`, `AgentRuntimeSpec`, `AgentRuntimeStatus`, `SandboxTemplate`, and `AgentRuntimeList` shall be properly defined\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: AgentRuntime struct embedding\nGIVEN an AgentRuntime instance\nWHEN accessing metadata\nTHEN metav1.TypeMeta and metav1.ObjectMeta shall be embedded\n\n// Scenario 2: AgentRuntimeSpec required fields\nGIVEN an AgentRuntimeSpec\nWHEN validating the spec\nTHEN Ports (targetPort in JSON), Template (podTemplate in JSON), SessionTimeout, and MaxSessionDuration shall be required\n\n// Scenario 3: AgentRuntimeSpec default values\nGIVEN an AgentRuntimeSpec without timeout values\nWHEN kubebuilder applies defaults\nTHEN SessionTimeout shall default to \"15m\" AND MaxSessionDuration shall default to \"8h\"\n\n// Scenario 4: AgentRuntimeStatus conditions\nGIVEN an AgentRuntimeStatus\nWHEN accessing Conditions\nTHEN it shall be a slice of metav1.Condition with atomic list type\n\n// Scenario 5: SandboxTemplate PodSpec\nGIVEN a SandboxTemplate\nWHEN creating a sandbox pod\nTHEN Spec field shall contain corev1.PodSpec for the pod definition\n\n// Scenario 6: AgentRuntime DeepCopy\nGIVEN an AgentRuntime with populated fields\nWHEN calling DeepCopy()\nTHEN a deep copy with identical values shall be returned\nAND modifying nested maps/slices in the copy shall not affect the original\n\n// Scenario 7: AgentRuntime DeepCopyObject\nGIVEN an AgentRuntime instance\nWHEN calling DeepCopyObject()\nTHEN it shall return a runtime.Object that is a deep copy\n\n// Scenario 8: AgentRuntimeList DeepCopy\nGIVEN an AgentRuntimeList with items\nWHEN calling DeepCopy()\nTHEN items slice shall be deeply copied\n\n// Scenario 9: AgentRuntime JSON field names\nGIVEN an AgentRuntimeSpec marshaled to JSON\nWHEN inspecting the JSON\nTHEN \"targetPort\" shall be used for Ports field AND \"podTemplate\" shall be used for Template field\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-008: CodeInterpreter CRD Types\n\n**GIVEN** CodeInterpreter represents a specialized runtime for code execution  \n**WHEN** defining the CRD structure  \n**THEN** `CodeInterpreter`, `CodeInterpreterSpec`, `CodeInterpreterStatus`, `CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate`, and `CodeInterpreterList` shall be properly defined\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: CodeInterpreter struct embedding\nGIVEN a CodeInterpreter instance\nWHEN accessing metadata\nTHEN metav1.TypeMeta and metav1.ObjectMeta shall be embedded\n\n// Scenario 2: CodeInterpreterSpec required fields\nGIVEN a CodeInterpreterSpec\nWHEN validating the spec\nTHEN Template field shall be required\n\n// Scenario 3: CodeInterpreterSpec default values\nGIVEN a CodeInterpreterSpec without defaults\nWHEN kubebuilder applies defaults\nTHEN SessionTimeout shall default to \"15m\" AND MaxSessionDuration shall default to \"8h\" AND AuthMode shall default to \"picod\"\n\n// Scenario 4: CodeInterpreterSpec optional fields\nGIVEN a CodeInterpreterSpec\nWHEN optional fields are not set\nTHEN Ports, WarmPoolSize, and AuthMode may be nil/empty\n\n// Scenario 5: CodeInterpreterSpec AuthMode validation\nGIVEN a CodeInterpreterSpec\nWHEN setting AuthMode\nTHEN kubebuilder shall only accept \"picod\" or \"none\" values\n\n// Scenario 6: CodeInterpreterStatus Ready field\nGIVEN a CodeInterpreterStatus\nWHEN accessing Ready field\nTHEN it shall be a boolean indicating readiness\n\n// Scenario 7: CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate image field\nGIVEN a CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate\nWHEN specifying container image\nTHEN Image field shall be available (optional with empty string default)\n\n// Scenario 8: CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate resource fields\nGIVEN a CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate\nWHEN configuring the container\nTHEN RuntimeClassName, ImagePullPolicy, ImagePullSecrets, Environment, Command, Args, and Resources shall be available\n\n// Scenario 9: CodeInterpreter DeepCopy\nGIVEN a CodeInterpreter with populated fields\nWHEN calling DeepCopy()\nTHEN a deep copy with identical values shall be returned\nAND modifying nested pointers in the copy shall not affect the original\n\n// Scenario 10: CodeInterpreter DeepCopyObject\nGIVEN a CodeInterpreter instance\nWHEN calling DeepCopyObject()\nTHEN it shall return a runtime.Object that is a deep copy\n\n// Scenario 11: CodeInterpreterList DeepCopy\nGIVEN a CodeInterpreterList with items\nWHEN calling DeepCopy()\nTHEN items slice shall be deeply copied\n```\n\n---\n\n### REQ-009: Kubernetes API Machinery Integration\n\n**GIVEN** types must integrate with Kubernetes API machinery  \n**WHEN** generating client code and CRD manifests  \n**THEN** proper kubebuilder markers and deepcopy-gen markers shall be present\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```go\n// Scenario 1: AgentRuntime runtime.Object implementation\nGIVEN the generated zz_generated.deepcopy.go\nWHEN checking AgentRuntime\nTHEN it shall implement runtime.Object interface via DeepCopyObject\n\n// Scenario 2: CodeInterpreter runtime.Object implementation\nGIVEN the generated zz_generated.deepcopy.go\nWHEN checking CodeInterpreter\nTHEN it shall implement runtime.Object interface via DeepCopyObject\n\n// Scenario 3: Kubebuilder resource scope\nGIVEN AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter types\nWHEN generating CRD manifests\nTHEN both shall have Namespaced scope\n\n// Scenario 4: Kubebuilder status subresource\nGIVEN AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter types\nWHEN generating CRD manifests\nTHEN both shall have status subresource enabled\n\n// Scenario 5: Kubebuilder printcolumn\nGIVEN AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter types\nWHEN generating CRD manifests\nTHEN \"Age\" column shall be displayed from .metadata.creationTimestamp\n```\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `shared_types.go` | ProtocolType, AuthModeType, TargetPort definitions |\n| `agentruntime_types.go` | AgentRuntime, AgentRuntimeSpec, AgentRuntimeStatus, SandboxTemplate, AgentRuntimeList |\n| `codeinterpreter_types.go` | CodeInterpreter, CodeInterpreterSpec, CodeInterpreterStatus, CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate, CodeInterpreterList |\n| `groupversion_info.go` | GroupVersion, SchemeBuilder, AddToScheme |\n| `register.go` | Kind constants, GroupVersionKind helpers, Resource helper |\n| `zz_generated.deepcopy.go` | Generated DeepCopy implementations |\n| `types_test.go` | Unit tests for all types |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- `k8s.io/api/core/v1` - Core Kubernetes API types (PodSpec, etc.)\n- `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` - ObjectMeta, TypeMeta, Duration, Condition\n- `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime` - runtime.Object interface\n- `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime/schema` - GroupVersion, GroupVersionResource\n- `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/scheme` - SchemeBuilder\n\n---\n\n## Validation Checklist\n\n- [ ] All type constants have correct string values\n- [ ] All structs have correct JSON tags for Kubernetes API\n- [ ] All kubebuilder markers are present for CRD generation\n- [ ] DeepCopy methods correctly deep-copy all nested structures\n- [ ] DeepCopyObject returns correct type for runtime.Object interface\n- [ ] GroupVersion matches API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`\n- [ ] Resource helper returns correct GroupVersionResource\n- [ ] All unit tests in `types_test.go` pass","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types_test.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/groupversion_info.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775840769687,"end":1775840769696}}}}
